Linked Discourses 25
1. The Eye
8. Craving For Sights
At Sāvatthī.
“Mendicants, craving for sights is impermanent, perishing, and changing.
Craving for sounds,
craving for smells,
craving for tastes,
craving for touches,
and craving for thoughts are impermanent, perishing, and changing.
Someone who has faith and confidence in these principles is called a follower by faith. …”


